**Google Hacking / Google Dorks**
Google Dorking (Google Hacking) is a technique where you use advanced search operators in Google to find sensitive or hidden information that is publicly indexed.

👉 Professionals use it in passive reconnaissance (OSINT) to discover:

Exposed files (PDFs, configs, backups)
Login pages
Admin panels
Sensitive directories
Public credentials (misconfigured systems)


🧠 Core Google Dorking Operators (Must Know)
1. Basic Operators
site:example.com    → Search only inside a domain
inurl:admin         → URL contains "admin"
intitle:"index of"  → Directory listing pages
filetype:pdf        → Specific file types
cache:              → View cached version

🔥 Some Powerful Google Dorks (Used by Professionals)
📂 Find Open Directories
intitle:"index of"
intitle:"index of" "backup"
intitle:"index of" "parent directory"

👉 Finds exposed folders like:

backups
logs
uploads

🔑 Find Login Pages / Admin Panels
inurl:admin
inurl:login
intitle:"admin panel"
site:example.com inurl:admin

📄 Find Sensitive Files
filetype:env DB_PASSWORD
filetype:log "error"
filetype:sql "dump"
filetype:txt "username" "password"

🗄️ Find Configuration Files
filetype:xml "config"
filetype:json "api_key"
filetype:ini "password"

🌐 Find Subdomains
site:*.example.com

📷 Find Cameras / IoT Devices (Shodan-style via Google)
inurl:view.shtml
intitle:"Live View / - AXIS"

💳 Find Exposed Credentials (⚠️ Ethical Use Only)
"username" "password" filetype:xls
"login" "password" filetype:csv
